body.name: GAMEMAX 750W Fully Modular ARGB Power Supply, ATX3.0 & PCIE 5.0, 80 Plus Gold Certified, 105°C Japanese Caps, ATX Gaming Power Supply
features: 80 Plus Gold Certified: 750W power supply delivers 90% or higher efficiency under typical loads. Achieve power savings and reduced heat, ensuring peak performance while cutting costs.

ATX 3.0 & PCIe 5.0 Ready: It allows a remarkable 200% total power excursion and 300% GPU power excursion, ensuring full compatibility with high-performance NVIDIA 40 series graphics cards. The package includes a 12VHPWR Cable for hassle-free installation and future upgrades.
100% Japanese Capacitors: Crafted with premium Japanese capacitors for long-lasting reliability and stable output with 5V/3.3V DC-DC. Offering peace of mind with a 5-year warranty.
ARGB SYNC: Elevate your rig's style with ARGB SYNC, seamlessly integrating vibrant lighting effects with the A-RGB software of most mainstream motherboards.
Whisper-Quiet Fan: The ATX power supply is equipped with a 140mm ultra-quiet fan that maintains excellent heat dissipation without producing disturbing noise.
Fully Modular: 750 watt power supply features a fully modular design that optimizes airflow and minimizes clutter. Enjoy seamless organization.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Slow shipping was the only flaw.
reviews.reviewText: Other than taking two weeks to ship, i had no issues with this purchase. it worked great and the colors were synced up with my motherboard without any software. i would recommend this PSU, but only if you arent in a hurry to build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I LOVE this Power Supply!! Great Bang for Your Buck and is Silent as a Prius! 10/10
reviews.reviewText: I came across this power supply on Amazon since my local computer part store was completely out of 800 W power supplies. After reading the reviews for this power supply and other ones they offer, I decided to give it chance and the rest is history! To give context...I was using a 10 year old 800 W power supply for my rig and that thing was LOUD. I almost want to compare it to a jet engine because of how loud it would run. However for this power supply, it's easily cut down the fan noise by 85% - 90% and I can actually sleep at night now if I leave it on to download games! Haha.In regards to performance, it holds up extremely well when I play graphic demanding games on my rig. I've been playing a lot of Battlefront 2 lately on max settings as well as Division 2. I have had zero issues while gaming period. No crashing, choppiness, or hiccups. Although I first was unsure about the build quality or material, it has held up perfectly!Finally, I love the color!!! It fits perfect for the case on my gaming rig. All in all I'm very impressed! Definitely would consider purchasing another power supply from this brand again. :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Initial installation was good. Powered on just fine and is holding pretty steady.
reviews.reviewText: The install went well. So far, everything's holding pretty stable. I'm waiting to upgrade to a higher end GPU, so right now it's not really straining with my RX580. Extra cables could be just a bit longer.Pic shows active pc. Don't have any of the unit itself. It's tucked away pretty good.I'll give it another week as it's only been running for a couple of days.Pros:- Clean cut, sharp looking- Stable power, extra cables are of quality build- Quiet so farCons:- Spare blue CPU port is not addressed in manual and no cable provided. I could have used that cable to supply the additional 4 pin header that is currently blank. Not a huge con, but it's apparent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great PSU for the $
reviews.reviewText: I have it in a Thermaltake Tower 500 Snow Edition so unless you're sitting low you can only see the light from the side, that's the cases problem not the PSU. It has plenty of modular connectors and one for the A-RGB (3PIN) light, if you don't have a 3pin it has a button next to the power switch that lets you cycle through all the different light effects and colors. It's also the pretty quiet it powers a RTX 3080Ti and I9-10900k, 12 fans and AIO-CPU cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was upgrading my GPU from a 1050ti to a 3060. My existing PSU wasn't going to cut it.I wanted a PSU that would have plenty of power for a 3060 but not be silly money. My case doesn't have to look like a work of art, the fact that this has RGB wasn't really relevant for me, the power and the price was all I was interested in.It does exactly what I need and the price was right, no regrets. A good buy.

reviews.reviewTitle: Ist halt ein Netzteil mit RGB
reviews.reviewText: Bisher ist es noch nicht in Flammen aufgegangen, die Kabel sind ganz okay und ausreichend variiert und über einen Knopf auf der Rückseite kann man den RGB-Modus ohne Werkzeug einstellen.Leider kann man das Netzteil nicht als exhaust montieren wenn man die bezahlte Beleuchtung sehen möchte (daher wird auch der Staubfilter am Boden nicht genutzt). Zudem sind die Kabel für die CPU auf der Netzteilseite extrem hässlich blau, das hätte nicht sein müssen.
